- Create: `apps/control-web/package.json`
- Create: `apps/control-web/tsconfig.json`
- Create: `apps/control-web/vite.config.ts`
- Create: `apps/control-web/index.html`
- Create: `apps/control-web/src/api.ts`
- Create: `apps/control-web/src/pages/opportunity-page.tsx`
- Create: `apps/control-web/src/router.tsx`
- Create: `apps/control-web/src/main.tsx`
- Create: `apps/control-web/src/styles.css`
- Test: `tests/smoke/control-web.test.tsx`

Step 1: Write the failing smoke test for the control form:
```tsx
import { fireEvent, render, screen } from '@testing-library/react';
import { describe, expect, it } from 'vitest';
import { OpportunityPage } from '../../apps/control-web/src/pages/opportunity-page';

describe('control-web', () => {
  it('submits an opportunity and shows the generated report link', async () => {
    const api = {
      createOpportunity: async () => ({
        id: 'opp_001',
        slug: 'ai-coding-model-procurement-options',
        title: 'AI Coding Model Procurement Options',
        market: 'global',
        input: {
          title: 'AI Coding Model Procurement Options',
          query: 'best ai coding models',
          market: 'global',
          audience: 'engineering leads',
          problem: 'Teams need to compare price and routing options',
          outcome: 'Produce a minimal report shell'
        },
        status: 'draft' as const,
        createdAt: '2026-03-27T12:00:00.000Z'
      }),
      compileOpportunity: async () => ({
        opportunity: {
          id: 'opp_001',
          slug: 'ai-coding-model-procurement-options',
          title: 'AI Coding Model Procurement Options',
          market: 'global',
          input: {
            title: 'AI Coding Model Procurement Options',
            query: 'best ai coding models',
            market: 'global',
            audience: 'engineering leads',
            problem: 'Teams need to compare price and routing options',
            outcome: 'Produce a minimal report shell'
          },
          status: 'compiled' as const,
          createdAt: '2026-03-27T12:00:00.000Z'
        },
        tasks: [
          {
            id: 'task_001',
            opportunityId: 'opp_001',
            kind: 'collect-evidence' as const,
            status: 'ready' as const
          },
          {
            id: 'task_002',
            opportunityId: 'opp_001',
            kind: 'score-opportunity' as const,
            status: 'ready' as const
          },
          {
            id: 'task_003',
            opportunityId: 'opp_001',
            kind: 'render-report' as const,
            status: 'ready' as const
          }
        ],
        workflow: {
          id: 'wf_001',
          opportunityId: 'opp_001',
          taskIds: ['task_001', 'task_002', 'task_003'],
          status: 'ready' as const
        },
        report: {
          id: 'report_001',
          opportunityId: 'opp_001',
          title: 'AI Coding Model Procurement Options',
          summary: 'Minimal report shell',
          sections: [
            {
              id: 'sec_001',
              title: 'Why this topic now',
              body: 'Demand is rising.'
            }
          ],
          createdAt: '2026-03-27T12:00:00.000Z'
        }
      })
    };

    render(
      <OpportunityPage
        api={api}
        reportBaseUrl="http://localhost:3002"
      />
    );

    fireEvent.change(screen.getByLabelText(/title/i), {
      target: { value: 'AI Coding Model Procurement Options' }
    });
    fireEvent.change(screen.getByLabelText(/query/i), {
      target: { value: 'best ai coding models' }
    });
    fireEvent.change(screen.getByLabelText(/market/i), {
      target: { value: 'global' }
    });
    fireEvent.change(screen.getByLabelText(/audience/i), {
      target: { value: 'engineering leads' }
    });
    fireEvent.change(screen.getByLabelText(/problem/i), {
      target: { value: 'Teams need to compare price and routing options' }
    });
    fireEvent.change(screen.getByLabelText(/outcome/i), {
      target: { value: 'Produce a minimal report shell' }
    });
    fireEvent.click(screen.getByRole('button', { name: /compile report shell/i }));

    expect(
      await screen.findByRole('link', { name: /open report shell/i })
    ).toHaveAttribute('href', 'http://localhost:3002/reports/report_001');
  });
});
```

Step 2: Run and verify failure:
`pnpm test -- tests/smoke/control-web.test.tsx`
Expected: FAIL because `OpportunityPage` and the control app do not exist yet.

Step 3: Create the Vite app shell and API client.
`apps/control-web/package.json`:
- name `@openfons/control-web`
- private true
- version `0.1.0`
- type `module`
- scripts: `dev`, `build`, `lint`, `typecheck`, `preview`
- dependencies: `@openfons/contracts workspace:*`, `@tanstack/react-router ^1.114.25`, `react ^19.0.0`, `react-dom ^19.0.0`
- devDependencies: `@types/react ^19.0.10`, `@types/react-dom ^19.0.4`, `@vitejs/plugin-react ^4.4.1`, `vite ^6.2.2`, `vite-tsconfig-paths ^5.1.4`

`apps/control-web/tsconfig.json`:
- extends `../../tsconfig.base.json`
- compilerOptions: `module: ESNext`, `moduleResolution: Bundler`, `noEmit: true`
- include `src/**/*`, `vite.config.ts`

`vite.config.ts`:
```ts
import { defineConfig } from 'vite';
import react from '@vitejs/plugin-react';
import tsconfigPaths from 'vite-tsconfig-paths';

export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [react(), tsconfigPaths()]
});
```

`index.html` title `OpenFons Control`, root div, module script `/src/main.tsx`.

`src/api.ts`:
- export type `ControlApi` with `createOpportunity` and `compileOpportunity`
- export `createControlApi(baseUrl)` using `fetch`
- POST create endpoint with JSON body, throw `Failed to create opportunity` on non-ok, return `{ opportunity }.opportunity`
- POST compile endpoint, throw `Failed to compile opportunity` on non-ok, return parsed `CompilationResult`

Step 4: Implement `apps/control-web/src/pages/opportunity-page.tsx` exactly as the planРђЎs minimum UI:
- imports `useState`, `FormEvent`, `CompilationResult`, `OpportunityInput`, `createControlApi`, `ControlApi`
- props `{ api?: ControlApi; reportBaseUrl?: string }`
- `initialForm` has empty strings for title/query/market/audience/problem/outcome
- default `api = createControlApi(import.meta.env.VITE_CONTROL_API_BASE_URL ?? 'http://localhost:3001')`
- default `reportBaseUrl = import.meta.env.VITE_REPORT_WEB_BASE_URL ?? 'http://localhost:3002'`
- local state for `form`, `result`, `submitting`, `error`
- `updateField` helper
- `submit` prevents default, sets submitting/error, create then compile, store result, on error show message, finally clear submitting
- render main panel with eyebrow `OpenFons Control Plane`, heading `Compile the first report shell`, lede text, form with labeled Title/Query/Market/Audience/Problem/Outcome fields, submit button text `Compiling...` or `Compile report shell`, error paragraph when set
- when result exists, render second panel with heading `Compilation ready`, report summary, workflow task count, and link href `${reportBaseUrl}/reports/${result.report.id}` labeled `Open report shell`

Step 5: Add router, entry point, styles exactly as plan:
- `src/router.tsx` uses `createRootRoute`, `createRoute`, `createRouter`, `Outlet`, root layout only renders `<Outlet />`, index route `/` renders `OpportunityPage`, export `router`, declare Register module
- `src/main.tsx` renders `RouterProvider` in `React.StrictMode`, imports `./styles.css`
- `src/styles.css` use the plan's minimal stylesheet values and selectors from the task

Step 6: Install dependencies and verify:
- `pnpm install`
- `pnpm test -- tests/smoke/control-web.test.tsx`
- `pnpm --filter @openfons/control-web build`
- `pnpm --filter @openfons/control-web lint`
Expected: React deps install, smoke test passes, Vite build succeeds, TS no errors.

Step 7: Commit:
- `git add apps/control-web tests/smoke/control-web.test.tsx pnpm-lock.yaml`
- `git commit -m "feat(control-web): add opportunity compile shell"`

